18:21.750 --> 18:22.917
Maybe.

18:23.000 --> 18:25.834
You two are the most
self-destructive,

18:25.917 --> 18:28.542
crazy motherfuckers
that I've ever met!

18:31.959 --> 18:35.125
Just us now, Mick.

18:40.834 --> 18:43.500
It's a statement.

18:43.583 --> 18:45.250
Saying that Ray told you

18:45.333 --> 18:48.041
that he killed Agent Van Miller.

18:48.125 --> 18:50.750
What, you think
I'd let that go?

18:50.834 --> 18:51.709
The murder of a brother agent?

18:51.792 --> 18:53.750
(quiet laugh)

18:53.834 --> 18:56.125
You want to pin it on Ray?

18:56.208 --> 18:57.875
Sign the statement.

18:57.959 --> 18:59.709
I'll send you back to Mexico.

19:02.000 --> 19:04.625
I'm not ratting out my son!

19:04.709 --> 19:07.583
Go fuck yourself.

19:10.000 --> 19:12.291
Okay, Mick.

19:14.333 --> 19:15.875
Enjoy the view.

19:15.959 --> 19:17.583
(door opens)

19:21.208 --> 19:22.709
Can I get some more bullets?

19:24.667 --> 19:26.417
Really getting
your target practice in today.

19:27.625 --> 19:29.291
Yeah. Listen.

19:29.375 --> 19:31.333
There's a cop who shoots here
sometimes, um...

19:31.417 --> 19:33.166
Uh, lots of cops shoot here.

19:33.250 --> 19:35.417
Is there a specific one
that you're interested in?

19:36.917 --> 19:38.333
You know, forget the bullets.
I-I got to go.

19:42.000 --> 19:44.792
Thanks.

19:44.875 --> 19:46.959
Oh.

19:50.709 --> 19:52.000
DEB: Hello?

19:52.083 --> 19:53.041
Hey, Deb.

19:53.125 --> 19:53.917
Hi, Abby.

19:54.000 --> 19:55.667
I want to see
the Trousdale house.

19:55.750 --> 19:57.583
Don't tell me you're having
second thoughts.

19:57.667 --> 19:59.667
No, I-I, I just want to see it.

19:59.750 --> 20:01.542
Can I get in?

20:01.625 --> 20:04.709
Cochran's holding him at the
FBI building in Westwood.

20:04.792 --> 20:05.458
We need to get him
out of there.

20:05.542 --> 20:07.583
We need a
superior court judge.

20:07.667 --> 20:08.583
You know one?

20:08.667 --> 20:10.583
Of course. He's a dear friend.

20:10.667 --> 20:11.083
What's his name?

20:11.166 --> 20:11.875
Raymond, I can't.

20:11.959 --> 20:14.458
I need a name, Ezra.

20:14.542 --> 20:15.542
He's a religious man!

20:15.625 --> 20:19.250
We study Torah together.
He won't break the law.

20:19.333 --> 20:20.375
I'll convince him.

20:20.458 --> 20:21.083
Tikkun olam.

20:21.166 --> 20:22.959
We've committed enough sins.

20:23.041 --> 20:25.417
Mickey's talking
to Cochran.

20:25.500 --> 20:26.709
He could tell him everything.

20:26.792 --> 20:28.709
Sean Walker, Van Miller,

20:28.792 --> 20:30.583
Black Mass, Colleen.

20:30.667 --> 20:32.166
We could go to jail, Ezra.

20:32.250 --> 20:33.458
Irving Salzman.

20:35.041 --> 20:38.709
(door opens)
I feel dirty.

20:38.792 --> 20:40.709
(hip-hop music playing)

20:43.959 --> 20:46.834
(indistinct chatter)

20:49.208 --> 20:50.792
Hey, there's Cookie.

20:52.333 --> 20:54.000
He just got home.

20:54.083 --> 20:56.041
From where?
I thought he was from L.A.

20:56.125 --> 20:57.166
(laughs) No.

20:57.250 --> 20:58.166
Prison, Shawty.

20:58.250 --> 21:01.166
Come on, let's say hi.

21:01.250 --> 21:04.583
Hey, Cookie!

21:04.667 --> 21:05.959
Boy, I love the way
you sing, my nigga.

21:06.041 --> 21:07.000
Hey. Thanks for these.

21:07.083 --> 21:09.041
It's three carats, baby.

21:09.125 --> 21:10.000
I want you to know I
appreciate the talent.

21:10.083 --> 21:13.458
This is my girl, Bridget.

21:13.542 --> 21:15.083
Hi.

21:15.166 --> 21:18.083
How you doing, snowflake?

21:19.208 --> 21:20.709
You know what that is?

21:20.792 --> 21:23.166
Glock 45.

21:23.250 --> 21:23.709
My dad has one.

21:23.792 --> 21:24.792
(laughs)

21:24.875 --> 21:27.125
What is he a cop?

21:27.208 --> 21:29.458
Not exactly.
Well, look here.

21:29.542 --> 21:30.208
You stay away from
guns, all right?

21:30.291 --> 21:33.792
(laughs)
Me and you, young fella?

21:33.875 --> 21:35.959
We need to talk
business real soon.

21:36.041 --> 21:38.125
Any time.

21:40.125 --> 21:41.375
She's cute.

21:41.458 --> 21:42.542
I know.

21:44.417 --> 21:45.208
Yeah, I don't, uh, think

21:45.291 --> 21:48.166
I'll be late tonight,
sweetheart.

21:48.250 --> 21:50.083
I have got a conference
this afternoon,

21:50.166 --> 21:52.542
but I don't think
that should go...

21:54.417 --> 21:56.375
WOMAN:
Irving?

21:56.458 --> 21:58.083
Are you there?

21:58.166 --> 22:00.709
(gasps) Um...

22:00.792 --> 22:03.375
I have to call you back.

22:03.458 --> 22:04.542
What is this?

22:10.291 --> 22:12.709
God!

22:12.792 --> 22:14.709
(cell phone ringing)

22:16.000 --> 22:18.458
Ezra, listen.

22:18.542 --> 22:20.000
Something terrible's
happened and...

22:20.083 --> 22:22.250
Irving, how could you?!

22:22.333 --> 22:23.583
How could I what?

22:23.667 --> 22:25.000
How could you send me this?!

22:25.083 --> 22:26.750
These are children!

22:26.834 --> 22:28.667
Do you know the danger
you've put me in?!

22:28.750 --> 22:29.333
Ezra, believe me.

22:29.417 --> 22:31.041
I didn't send this to you!

22:31.125 --> 22:33.583
This is some horrible mistake!

22:33.667 --> 22:34.792
It's a virus.

22:34.875 --> 22:37.250
What... what do I do?!
Calm down, calm, calm down.

22:37.333 --> 22:38.083
I know someone who can help you.

22:38.166 --> 22:40.166
I'll send him right over.

22:40.250 --> 22:42.625
You're a mensch.

22:43.834 --> 22:45.959
He's ready.

22:47.875 --> 22:48.375
Ray?

22:48.458 --> 22:51.959
He only pledged $5,000

22:52.041 --> 22:53.667
to the RGOCC.

22:53.750 --> 22:55.709
Squeeze him for another 20.

22:55.792 --> 22:57.583
I'll see what I can do.

23:18.875 --> 23:20.375
JUDY:
Hi, there.

23:20.458 --> 23:23.333
I saw your car
in the driveway.

23:23.417 --> 23:25.333
This is Lisa.
Hi.

23:25.417 --> 23:27.125
Hi.

23:27.208 --> 23:29.792
We got off on the wrong
foot the other day.

23:29.875 --> 23:31.458
Peace offering?

23:31.542 --> 23:33.041
(laughs) Sure.

23:33.125 --> 23:34.875
Why not?

23:34.959 --> 23:36.750
Let me find some glasses.

23:36.834 --> 23:40.667
It really is
a beautiful house.

23:40.750 --> 23:42.500
(door opens)

23:52.000 --> 23:54.375
This woman's body was found
in the oil fields

23:54.458 --> 23:56.625
two days ago.

23:56.709 --> 23:59.625
Why don't you tell me
what you know about her?

23:59.709 --> 24:01.208
I've never seen her
before in my life.

24:01.291 --> 24:04.166
Really?

24:04.250 --> 24:05.041
A week before she died,
you were with her

24:05.125 --> 24:07.625
at the, uh...

24:07.709 --> 24:08.166
the Four Seasons Spa.

24:08.250 --> 24:09.583
Don't ring a bell.

24:09.667 --> 24:13.583
Ballistics say the bullet
that killed her

24:13.667 --> 24:15.583
is a match to Sully's gun.

24:20.041 --> 24:21.542
Pretty, huh?

24:26.333 --> 24:29.500
Dogs were chewing on her.

24:29.583 --> 24:31.000
Did you fuck her, Mick?

24:31.083 --> 24:34.959
Yeah.

24:37.375 --> 24:39.834
But I didn't kill her.

24:39.917 --> 24:42.417
Sully did.
All comes back to Sully.

24:42.500 --> 24:44.250
And who brought Sully out here?

24:44.333 --> 24:45.709
Your fucking son.

24:45.792 --> 24:47.709
If he'd have left
Sully in Boston,

24:47.792 --> 24:51.458
she'd still be alive.

24:51.542 --> 24:53.375
And Van Miller.

24:53.458 --> 24:55.041
And Catherine Shaughnessy.

24:55.125 --> 24:55.875
And God knows how many more

24:55.959 --> 24:57.917
freaking bodies
are gonna pop up.

24:58.000 --> 24:59.375
Fucking Donovans,
you're like a...

24:59.458 --> 25:01.166
you're like a virus.

25:01.250 --> 25:03.709
She was a nice lady.

25:03.792 --> 25:05.834
She didn't deserve to
die the way she did.

25:05.917 --> 25:08.417
You don't deserve to spend
the rest of your life in prison.

25:08.500 --> 25:10.000
After all,
you've done your time.

25:10.083 --> 25:12.750
You bet I did.

25:12.834 --> 25:15.083
I can handle you, Mick.

25:15.166 --> 25:16.583
You're a simple man.

25:16.667 --> 25:20.125
You want to eat, drink,
fuck, enjoy your family.

25:20.208 --> 25:20.917
That's right.

25:21.000 --> 25:22.083
Maybe I don't need
to put you away.

25:22.166 --> 25:25.083
But Ray's a problem.

25:25.166 --> 25:26.500
He's out of control.

25:26.583 --> 25:30.083
And I'm not gonna
let him fuck up my plans.

25:30.166 --> 25:33.500
So, which one of you
goes to prison?

25:33.583 --> 25:33.792
You or Ray?

25:36.417 --> 25:39.333
You think about that, old man.

25:43.166 --> 25:45.375
I'll be back in an hour.

26:00.083 --> 26:02.834
I'm a religious man!
I don't visit that kind of site!

26:02.917 --> 26:04.917
I don't know how this

26:05.000 --> 26:05.959
got onto my computer!

26:06.041 --> 26:07.792
(spoofy '90s techno music plays
over laptop)

26:09.875 --> 26:11.166
Unfortunately, once it's
on your system,

26:11.250 --> 26:12.917
it's almost impossible
to get rid of it.

26:13.000 --> 26:14.083
Oh, my God.

26:14.166 --> 26:16.375
Ezra's pretty upset you put it
on his system as well.

26:16.458 --> 26:18.208
I didn't send this filth
to Ezra.

26:18.291 --> 26:21.166
I...
(sighs)

26:21.250 --> 26:22.125
Look...

26:22.208 --> 26:24.000
I have five grandchildren;
I worship them.

26:24.083 --> 26:26.333
You understand?

26:26.417 --> 26:27.709
This is the end of me;

26:27.792 --> 26:30.333
it's the end of my career.

26:30.417 --> 26:31.667
Oh, my God,

26:31.750 --> 26:33.583
what'll my wife think?

26:34.792 --> 26:35.208
(sighs)

26:35.291 --> 26:38.500
I didn't do this.

26:40.875 --> 26:42.375
I know you didn't.

26:44.792 --> 26:48.000
It's not gonna be easy,
but, uh...

26:48.083 --> 26:50.083
I can make this go away for you.

26:54.875 --> 26:57.375
You sons of bitches.

26:57.458 --> 27:00.709
What do you want?

27:00.792 --> 27:02.250
(women chuckling)
JUDY:
I want to do it.

27:02.333 --> 27:04.542
Oh, I, I-I need to
park my car.

27:04.625 --> 27:06.750
(laughing):
No...!

27:06.834 --> 27:08.583
(in Boston accent):
Park my car.

27:08.667 --> 27:10.709
(imitates accent):
Park my car.

27:10.792 --> 27:12.750
Yes, you're a Southie!

27:12.834 --> 27:13.959
(laughing):
Yes!

27:14.041 --> 27:14.375
(gasps)

27:14.458 --> 27:17.041
Oh, my God.

27:17.125 --> 27:18.041
I drank too fast,

27:18.125 --> 27:19.417
I think
I'm gonna throw up.

27:19.500 --> 27:21.041
Should we help you out
to your...

27:21.125 --> 27:22.083
(in Boston accent):
car...?

27:22.166 --> 27:22.458
(women laughing hysterically)

27:22.542 --> 27:24.250
Shut up!

27:24.333 --> 27:26.041
(gasps)
What?

27:26.125 --> 27:27.959
I'm sorry.

27:28.041 --> 27:29.542
(sighs)

27:29.625 --> 27:31.000
I don't feel good.

27:32.875 --> 27:34.500
I think this is a mistake;

27:34.583 --> 27:37.083
I-I don't even like this house

27:37.166 --> 27:38.709
anymore.

27:38.792 --> 27:39.875
Where do you shop?

27:39.959 --> 27:40.875
Where's the market?

27:40.959 --> 27:42.500
Where's the post office?

27:42.583 --> 27:43.542
Darling, it's Trousdale.

27:43.625 --> 27:45.250
I'm sure it's
a lot more convenient

27:45.333 --> 27:47.041
than Calabasas.

27:47.125 --> 27:49.458
But...

27:49.542 --> 27:50.709
it's not for everyone.

27:50.792 --> 27:53.417
What does that mean?

27:53.500 --> 27:54.458
We know all about
your husband.

27:54.542 --> 27:56.875
I mean, we know what he does.

27:56.959 --> 27:58.500
When you're ready
to ditch him,

27:58.583 --> 27:59.959
Blanche Blaylock is a

28:00.041 --> 28:01.291
personal friend of mine.

28:01.375 --> 28:02.500
She'll get you
a good deal.

28:02.583 --> 28:05.166
I'm not leaving
my fucking husband.

28:05.250 --> 28:07.000
Maybe that's what
you people do;

28:07.083 --> 28:08.542
where I come from,
we stick it out.

28:08.625 --> 28:10.542
Ray's a good provider--

28:10.625 --> 28:11.375
he's a loving father.

28:11.458 --> 28:12.625
Oh, honey,
let's face it...

28:12.709 --> 28:15.250
(laughing):
he's basically a street thug.

28:15.333 --> 28:17.750
(women screaming)

28:17.834 --> 28:21.583
(shouting): Who the fuck
do you think you are?!

28:21.667 --> 28:22.917
You let go of me!

28:23.000 --> 28:23.959
Call the police!

28:24.041 --> 28:25.291
Call the police.

28:25.375 --> 28:26.583
I'll call my fucking husband
and he'll kill you.

28:26.667 --> 28:28.834
JUDY:
You're in fucking trouble!

28:28.917 --> 28:30.458
You can't hurt me!

28:30.542 --> 28:31.500
(sighs)

28:31.583 --> 28:33.458
(gasps)

28:33.542 --> 28:35.625
(sighs)

28:43.667 --> 28:45.834
(panting)

28:45.917 --> 28:48.291
(phone clicking)

28:50.709 --> 28:52.709
Are you ready?

28:52.792 --> 28:54.291
Yeah, in a minute.

28:54.375 --> 28:55.166
Help me out here,
I can't...

28:55.250 --> 28:58.166
I can't reach.

28:58.250 --> 28:59.583
Come on.

29:00.333 --> 29:01.792
Last thing I need

29:01.875 --> 29:03.291
are for these things
to get infected.

29:03.375 --> 29:05.792
(sniffs)

29:05.875 --> 29:06.417
I usually...

29:06.500 --> 29:08.583
Get the bottom part, huh?

29:08.667 --> 29:09.709
(sighs)

29:09.792 --> 29:12.041
(grunts)
Yeah, that's it.

29:12.125 --> 29:13.208
Just get a...

29:13.291 --> 29:14.500
a little, uh,

29:14.583 --> 29:16.166
a little higher.

29:19.542 --> 29:21.917
I'm getting
tired of this.

29:22.000 --> 29:23.500
Really?

29:23.583 --> 29:25.000
So what?

29:25.333 --> 29:27.291
Come on.

29:27.375 --> 29:30.041
Let's go nail this

29:30.125 --> 29:31.667
leprechaun-loving
asshole.

29:34.041 --> 29:35.709
FBI AGENT:
This is an FBI operation.

29:35.792 --> 29:36.875
DETECTIVE:
We're stepping in.

29:36.959 --> 29:38.041
FBI AGENT:
Yeah, hold-hold on.

29:38.125 --> 29:39.125
DETECTIVE:
No, we're taking him.

29:39.208 --> 29:40.583
What the hell
is this?

29:40.667 --> 29:42.000
All right, what
is LAPD doing here?

29:42.083 --> 29:44.041
FBI AGENT:
You can't just come in here
and take a suspect.

29:44.125 --> 29:45.291
DETECTIVE:
I have a warrant, asshole.

29:45.375 --> 29:46.625
Whoa, what the fuck
is going on in here?

29:46.709 --> 29:48.166
LAPD,
we're taking him.

29:48.250 --> 29:49.375
No. No. No. This man
is in my custody.

29:49.458 --> 29:50.250
Have you
arrested him?

29:50.333 --> 29:51.125
We're holding him
for questioning.

29:51.208 --> 29:52.709
Mickey Donovan,
you're under arrest.

29:52.792 --> 29:53.834
I thought I already was.

29:53.917 --> 29:55.542
You have been remanded
into the custody of

29:55.625 --> 29:56.959
Judge Irving Salzman.
Whoa. Whoa. Whoa.
Whoa. Whoa. Whoa.

29:57.041 --> 29:58.041
You have the right
to remain silent;

29:58.125 --> 29:59.333
Hey! Hey!
anything you say can

29:59.417 --> 30:00.333
and will be
used against you...
Back the fuck off!

30:00.417 --> 30:01.542
Judge Salzman's declared him
a material witness

30:01.625 --> 30:03.625
for one of his cases.

30:03.709 --> 30:05.041
I don't give a shit.
I'm the fucking FBI!

30:05.125 --> 30:06.417
The judge's order
trumps your authority.

30:06.500 --> 30:08.542
Let's go.

30:08.625 --> 30:10.208
You, you got to be
kidding me.

30:10.291 --> 30:12.166
And if you try to stop us,
you'll be obstructing justice.

30:12.250 --> 30:13.208
Well, I'll fucking
have your badge, pal.

30:13.291 --> 30:15.375
You'll be working security
at fucking Home Depot!

30:15.458 --> 30:18.208
You got me wrong, pal.

30:18.291 --> 30:19.333
I'd never give up my son.

30:19.417 --> 30:20.417
Go fuck yourself.

30:20.500 --> 30:22.875
(phone chiming)

30:22.959 --> 30:24.542
(sighs)

30:24.625 --> 30:25.125
Donovan.

30:25.208 --> 30:27.291
(scoffs)

30:27.375 --> 30:29.375
You motherfucker.

30:29.458 --> 30:30.625
You motherfucker!

30:30.709 --> 30:32.250
Sorry to spoil your party,

30:32.333 --> 30:33.500
but I need to see my father.

30:33.583 --> 30:34.750
I don't know
how you did this,

30:34.834 --> 30:36.625
but I promise  you
I'm gonna nail you for it.

30:36.709 --> 30:38.583
No, you're not;
you're gonna thank me.

30:38.667 --> 30:40.750
(hip-hop music playing)

30:40.834 --> 30:43.250
(indistinct conversations)

30:43.333 --> 30:44.500
So, uh, how long

30:44.583 --> 30:45.375
have you known Cookie?

30:45.458 --> 30:48.041
Mm, couple weeks.

30:48.125 --> 30:50.667
Since he got out.

30:50.750 --> 30:53.250
Why do you think
he gave you these earrings?

30:53.333 --> 30:54.750
They must've been
really expensive.

30:54.834 --> 30:58.417
Shawty, when you a,
when you a star,

30:58.500 --> 31:00.083
you know,
people give you shit.

31:00.166 --> 31:02.417
Don't be all
cynical, girl,

31:02.500 --> 31:05.125
it's all love.

31:05.208 --> 31:06.500
GIRL (sweetly):
Hi, Marvin.

31:11.208 --> 31:13.041
(sighs)

31:15.166 --> 31:16.750
Hey, Bridg,
what's wrong?

31:17.709 --> 31:18.792
Why would you want me

31:18.875 --> 31:21.709
when you can have
girls like her?

31:22.458 --> 31:24.625
Who'd I give that
earring to...

31:24.709 --> 31:26.959
her or you?

31:28.166 --> 31:29.333
I'm gonna
show you something.

31:35.709 --> 31:38.667
(coughs, laughs)
(laughs)

31:42.375 --> 31:44.750
Where ya taking me,
back to my shithole?

31:44.834 --> 31:47.417
No, we got to do
something first.

31:47.500 --> 31:49.083
I stood by you, Ray.

31:49.166 --> 31:51.083
Didn't give you up.

31:51.166 --> 31:52.458
You know, I would
never do that.

31:52.542 --> 31:53.333
Sure you would.

31:53.417 --> 31:54.917
I just got you
out of there in time.

31:55.000 --> 31:56.625
Ray Ray, when are you
gonna realize

31:56.709 --> 31:58.667
that I'm not the devil?

31:58.750 --> 31:59.500
All right.

31:59.583 --> 32:01.667
(sighs)

32:01.750 --> 32:04.000
I'll give you a chance
to prove it.

32:04.083 --> 32:04.709
All you got to do is
tell a little story.

32:04.792 --> 32:07.917
What's in it for me?

32:08.000 --> 32:10.083
(scoffs)
Christ, Mick,

32:10.166 --> 32:11.041
what do you want?

32:11.125 --> 32:13.083
I don't want to
peel carrots no more.

32:13.166 --> 32:14.834
